The paper deals with reasoning over plots, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a hybrid approach that involves a table question-answering engine, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing models and proposes improvements, which could be relevant to information retrieval (IR) research.
